cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on mobile active authentication using multiple biometric and behavioral patterns. The paper discusses the collection and analysis of data from various sensors such as touch dynamics, accelerometer, gyroscope, WiFi, GPS location, and app usage. This suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with authentication and security. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of touch dynamics, which falls under the category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of accelerometer and gyroscope data could also suggest the paper could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of app usage data, which could suggest the paper could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
